<main class="container my-5">
    <article class="mb-5">
        <h2>RePET Global Expands Capacity in 2025</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">February 15, 2025</p>
        <p>We are excited to announce the expansion of our processing facility in Tunisia. With new state-of-the-art washing lines and sorting equipment, our capacity has increased by 30%. This means we can supply even more high-quality PET flakes to our customers. The expansion is part of our commitment to meet rising demand for recycled PET and to serve our partners better. <a href="#">Read more...</a></p>
    </article>
    <article class="mb-5">
        <h2>Partnership with EcoPlast Europe</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">January 10, 2025</p>
        <p>RePET Global has entered into a partnership with EcoPlast Europe, a leading plastic packaging manufacturer. This strategic collaboration will see our recycled PET flakes used in EcoPlast’s new line of sustainable packaging, replacing virgin plastic. We are proud to work together in reducing plastic waste and the carbon footprint of packaging. <a href="#">Read more...</a></p>
    </article>
    <article>
        <h2>Sustainability Milestone Achieved</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">December 1, 2024</p>
        <p>We have reached a significant milestone: over <strong>10,000 tons</strong> of PET bottles recycled since our inception. This achievement reflects our dedication to environmental responsibility. By converting what would have been waste into reusable material, we’ve prevented millions of bottles from ending up in landfills or oceans. Thank you to our team and partners for making this possible! <a href="#">Read more...</a></p>
    </article>
